# Leenk Static Files

Use `~/.scripts/leenk-static` as the only upload interface. Do not read, print,
copy, or persist the bearer token outside macOS Keychain.

## Authenticate

Run this only when the user explicitly approves rotating the production upload
credential:

```sh
~/.scripts/leenk-static auth
```

This generates a new token, saves it as the `leenk-static` generic password in
macOS Keychain, and updates the Worker's `STATIC_UPLOAD_TOKEN` secret. The old
token stops working.

## Upload

Upload to the file's basename:

```sh
~/.scripts/leenk-static upload ./document.pdf
```

Choose a nested public path:

```sh
~/.scripts/leenk-static upload ./report.pdf reports/2026/report.pdf
```

The command prints the public URL on success. Treat uploads as production
publishing: confirm the source file and destination, and do not overwrite an
existing public path unless the user requested it.

## Verify

Inspect metadata without downloading the body:

```sh
~/.scripts/leenk-static head reports/2026/report.pdf
```

Download or open the public URL with ordinary HTTP GET. Public URLs have this
shape:

```text
https://www.yusoofsh.id/static/reports/2026/report.pdf
```

## Constraints

- Require macOS `security`, `expect`, `openssl`, `curl`, `jq`, and `file`.
- Resolve the Worker project from `LEENK_REPO`, defaulting to
  `~/Developer/Community/leenk`.
