    61	
    62	## Static file hosting
    63	
    64	Files uploaded to `/static/<path>` are stored in the `leenk-static` R2 bucket and served directly
    65	from the same URL. Reads are public; uploads require the `STATIC_UPLOAD_TOKEN` Worker secret and
    66	accept a raw request body up to 100 MiB.
    67	
    68	Create the R2 bucket and upload secret once before the first deployment:
    69	
    70	```bash
    71	nub exec wrangler r2 bucket create leenk-static
    72	nub exec wrangler secret put STATIC_UPLOAD_TOKEN
    73	```
    74	
    75	Upload any binary file while preserving its media type:
    76	
    77	```bash
    78	curl https://www.yusoofsh.id/static/docs/guide.pdf \
    79	  -X POST \
    80	  -H "Authorization: Bearer $STATIC_UPLOAD_TOKEN" \
    81	  -H "Content-Type: application/pdf" \
    82	  --data-binary @guide.pdf
    83	```
    84	
    85	The same URL supports `GET` and `HEAD`. Uploading the same path again replaces the existing file.
    86	
    87	## Deployment
    88	
    89	The build produces an Astro server entry point and static assets in `dist/`. Preview the exact Worker configuration locally before deploying:
    90	
    91	```bash
    92	nub run build
    93	nub run preview
    94	```
    95	
    96	Production deployment is intentionally explicit:
